observations.recommendation:
Require the Municipal Treasurer to prepare a duly certified list showing the names of the taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year which data should come from the Real Property Tax Account Register (RPTAR) or Taxpayer’s Index Card maintained at the Municipal Treasurer’s Office; 

Furnish the Municipal Accountant a copy of the certified list to serve as the basis in recording the Real Property Tax Receivable and Special Education Tax Receivable accounts in the books; and

Require the Municipal Accountant to record the receivables based on the list furnished by the Municipal Treasurer in order to record in the books an accurate and verifiable data pursuant to Sections 19 and 20 of the NGAS Manual, Volume 1.

We recommended that Management, specifically the Bids and Awards Committee, submit a valid written explanation/justification on the deficiencies noted to prevent disallowance in audit:

	a. On why the procurement of one (1) unit Wheeled Excavator amounting to ₱12,489,996.60 was awarded to the supplier despite the unavailability of the item at the time of award;
	b. As to the undated Notice to Proceed and the Purchase Order upon its issuance and upon its receipt by the supplier;
	c. The reasons on why the BAC approved the request for extension (even twice) despite objection from the SB;
	d. Copy of SB Resolutions/ Municipal Mayor’s approval/disapproval on the request for time extensions of the supplier; and
	e. On the failure to impose liquidated damages amounting to ₱2,497,999.32 on the delayed delivery of the equipment, otherwise the BAC maybe held liable therefor.

We recommended that Management submit the following documents to support validity and propriety of the payments made to Jamaican Catering Services totaling ₱1,008,035.00 to prevent disallowance in audit, viz:

Duly Notarized letter- authority by the Municipal Coordinator to sign in the Purchase Orders and to receive payments/sign in the disbursement vouchers in behalf of Jamaican’s Catering Services;
A valid written explanation by the Bids and Awards Committee on why the procurements were split and procured thru Shopping instead of thru public bidding;
c. Valid documents such as:
   -Statements of   Accounts/Bills;
  -Properly numbered and dated POs., PR, RFQ, and Inspection Report;
-Minutes of meetings/conferences;
   -Program/Schedule of Activities;
-  List of Speakers;
- Certificate of Registration with the Department of Trade and Industry;
   -  Business/Mayor’s Permit; 
   - Annual Income Tax Return and Audited Financial Statements duly received by the Bureau of Internal Revenue (BIR); and
   - Authority to Print Official Receipts from the BIR.

